Sentencas: Herein, the spinel oxide CuBi2O4 is prepared by solid-state reaction method and characterized for the first time as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Electrode properties of CuBi2O4 spinel oxide as a new and potential cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: CuBi2O4 (CBO) crystallizes in tetragonal structure and is chemically compatible with Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.9 (GDC) electrolyte at 800 degrees C. Electrical conductivity relaxation is conducted to assess the oxygen surface exchange coefficient k(chem) and oxygen bulk diffusion coefficient D-chem of CBO material.
Titulo: Electrode properties of CuBi2O4 spinel oxide as a new and potential cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is found that CBO exhibits better oxygen transport properties than the traditional La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 (LSM) and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) cathodes.
Titulo: Electrode properties of CuBi2O4 spinel oxide as a new and potential cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical activity of CBO-based cathode is investigated by impedance spectroscopy on the symmetric cell with GDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Electrode properties of CuBi2O4 spinel oxide as a new and potential cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The CBO cathode forms good contact with the GDC electrolyte and displays low polarization resistance (RP) values, e.g., 0.58 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Electrode properties of CuBi2O4 spinel oxide as a new and potential cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The introducing GDC to form a composite cathode with CBO further reduces the RP to 0.39 Omega cm(2).
Titulo: Electrode properties of CuBi2O4 spinel oxide as a new and potential cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An anode-supported single cell with the CBO-GDC cathode exhibits a peak power density of 507 mWcm(-2) at 750 degrees C, suggesting the viability of CBO oxide as a cathode material for IT-SOFC.
Titulo: Electrode properties of CuBi2O4 spinel oxide as a new and potential cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells
